[3
Date: Mon, 14 Feb 2000 16:28:37 -0600
From: Dr. Lyle P. Vogel <LVogel@avma.org>

I believe the news report is a bit confused regarding vaccination against
tapeworm and ticks. The draft Pet Travel Scheme (Pilot Arrangements) Order,
Article 6 (4) states "animals will have to be treated for certain parasites
(the fox tapeworm, _Echinococcus multilocularis_, and ticks) to prevent a
risk of potentially serious zoonotic disease coming into the UK. This must
take place not less than 24 hours and not more than 48 hours before
embarkation for England."
--
Lyle P. Vogel, DVM, MPH
e-mail: LVogel@avma.org
